Definition: Remove all numbers with non-zero decimal value from the given list and return the resultant list. Return "[]" if the resultant list is empty.

Positive Examples.explanation: 796, 862, 424, 114 are the only numbers with no decimal values in the list.
All numbers in the list have non-zero decimal values, so an empty list is returned.

Negative Examples.explanation: The output contains numbers that are have non-zero decimal values.
The output rounded all of the numbers that are have non-zero decimal values to the closest integer.
